President Muhammadu Buhari will later on Monday begin an official visit to states affected by terrorism and other criminal activities. The states to be visited by the President, according to a statement issued by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, are Taraba, Benue, Zamfara, and Rivers. He will also visit Yobe State where 110 students of Government Girls Science and Technical College, Dapchi, were kidnapped by Boko Haram fighters. President Buhari had also tasked the Armed Forces and other security agencies to compile comprehensive reports on the various incidents. The statement reads: “From today, March 5, he will visit Taraba, and subsequently Benue, Yobe, Zamfara and Rivers States. “President Buhari has been receiving daily briefings, and has been in constant touch with the governors and has been updated with situation reports.” The President has also called on all Nigerians especially those in the affected areas to cooperate fully with the security agencies to enable them curb the spate of crimes, bring those responsible to justice and prevent further occurrences.  